    {
      "product_id": "fh2-on-premises",
      "product": "FH2 On-Premises",
      "url": "https://fh.dji.com/user-manual/en/release-notes/release-notes-private.html",
      "source_type": "fh2_html",
      "source_url": "https://fh.dji.com/user-manual/en/release-notes/release-notes-private.html",
      "language": "en",
      "date": "2026-04-29",
      "days_ago": 43,
      "version": "V1.5",
      "content_blocks": [
        {
          "type": "heading",
          "level": 2,
          "text": "2026-04-29 v1.5"
        },
        {
          "type": "heading",
          "level": 3,
          "text": "I. Functionality Alignment (Aligned to 2026-04-15)"
        },
        {
          "type": "heading",
          "level": 3,
          "text": "1、High-Definition Panorama"
        },
        {
          "type": "list",
          "items": [
            "DJI Dock 3 and Matrice 4 Enterprise now support 500MP high-definition panoramas for efficient one-click environment data collection.",
            "3× zoom can be set in the virtual cockpit and waypoint route settings to capture sphere panoramas. Automatic stitching is performed after capture. High-definition results can be viewed in the media file library, and support importing into the analyzer to use timeline and related features."
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "heading",
          "level": 3,
          "text": "2、Resource Library Upgrade"
        },
        {
          "type": "list",
          "items": [
            "The original media file library, model library, and design files have been merged into the \"Resource Library\" for unified, more convenient management.",
            "A recycle bin has been added. Deleted files are moved to the recycle bin first. Periodic auto-emptying can be configured to free up storage space."
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "heading",
          "level": 3,
          "text": "3、Multimodal Recognition for Flight Routes"
        },
        {
          "type": "list",
          "items": [
            "The task plan library now supports enabling multimodal recognition, allowing specified objects to be identified during flight route execution. Users are notified through designated methods when recognition is triggered."
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "heading",
          "level": 3,
          "text": "4、Surface Area Measurement in Analyzer"
        },
        {
          "type": "list",
          "items": [
            "Users can quickly measure the surface area of models, facilitating coverage area calculation and cost estimation, significantly improving efficiency in engineering operations.",
            "Applicable to scenarios such as earthwork covering, lawn greening, and irregularly curved architectural surfaces."
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "heading",
          "level": 3,
          "text": "5、FlightHub Sync"
        },
        {
          "type": "list",
          "items": [
            "FlightHub 2 FlightHub Sync Beta has completed testing and validation. It will be gradually phased out and replaced by the new FlightHub Sync.",
            "File Sync – Now supports cross-configuration of file type, project, and bucket. Multiple buckets can be configured simultaneously.",
            "Telemetry Data Sync – A new telemetry data sync feature enables real-time syncing of drone attitude data to third-party platforms.",
            "Livestream Forwarding – Now supports the RTSP protocol.",
            "Added support for Event API, allowing configuration of different event rules to push specific FlightHub events to external systems.",
            "File sync now supports automatically deleting source files within FlightHub after sync is complete.",
            "Third-Party Airspace Data Management – Supports configuring airspace information from third-party providers and displaying it within FlightHub."
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "heading",
          "level": 3,
          "text": "6、FlightHub Mapping API"
        },
        {
          "type": "list",
          "items": [
            "OpenAPI now includes the FlightHub Mapping API, enabling third-party systems to quickly integrate cloud-based mapping capabilities."
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "heading",
          "level": 3,
          "text": "7、Gaussian Splatting"
        },
        {
          "type": "list",
          "items": [
            "On-device reconstruction now supports Gaussian Splatting format, delivering more realistic and detailed results in scenes with fine structures and glass curtain walls."
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "heading",
          "level": 3,
          "text": "8、Model Sharing"
        },
        {
          "type": "list",
          "items": [
            "The model sharing page supports viewing via mobile phone or tablet scan without requiring login."
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "heading",
          "level": 3,
          "text": "9、Sync Annotations to Analyzer"
        },
        {
          "type": "list",
          "items": [
            "The analyzer map settings now support syncing project annotations, with the option to select annotations and convert them to measurements with one click."
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "heading",
          "level": 3,
          "text": "10、AirSense ICAO Filtering"
        },
        {
          "type": "list",
          "items": [
            "The \"Map Operation Area\" on the team page has been upgraded to \"Airspace Safety\", with new AirSense alert management capabilities, including support for filtering by ICAO number."
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "heading",
          "level": 3,
          "text": "11、AI Change Detection"
        },
        {
          "type": "list",
          "items": [
            "Media Change Detection: The media file library now supports intelligent detection and marking of change areas between two media folders generated by the same waypoint route task.",
            "Model Change Detection: The model library now supports intelligent detection and marking of change areas between two 2D models with overlapping areas."
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "heading",
          "level": 3,
          "text": "12、GCP-Based Reconstruction"
        },
        {
          "type": "list",
          "items": [
            "Cloud reconstruction now supports setting ground control points (GCPs). Standard targets support automatic point marking and automatic reconstruction."
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "heading",
          "level": 3,
          "text": "13、Real-Time Megaphone Support"
        },
        {
          "type": "list",
          "items": [
            "Supports initiating voice announcements and TTS announcements directly from the cloud."
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "heading",
          "level": 4,
          "text": "II. On-Premises Version Feature Optimizations"
        },
        {
          "type": "heading",
          "level": 3,
          "text": "1、Visual Deployment"
        },
        {
          "type": "list",
          "items": [
            "Supports completing the deployment of FlightHub, Terra, and 4G services in private environments through a visual interface, replacing traditional command-line and manual configuration methods.",
            "Helps customers shorten deployment cycles, lower implementation barriers, and improve deployment success rates. Applicable for initial deployment, first-time implementation, or operations where reduced deployment complexity is desired."
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "heading",
          "level": 3,
          "text": "2、Incremental Upgrade"
        },
        {
          "type": "list",
          "items": [
            "Starting from this version, incremental upgrades are supported. Compared to the previous full upgrade approach, only the necessary services that have changed need to be upgraded between adjacent versions, significantly reducing upgrade time and downtime.",
            "Note: This capability will take effect after the next version is released. Customers must first upgrade to this version, and can then use incremental upgrades when upgrading from this version to the next adjacent version."
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "heading",
          "level": 3,
          "text": "3、Permanent Data Deletion"
        },
        {
          "type": "list",
          "items": [
            "Starting from this version, files deleted from the media file library, model library, and design files will be permanently deleted, and the corresponding storage space will be released simultaneously."
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "heading",
          "level": 3,
          "text": "4、AIO Admin Console – New Visual Configuration Options"
        },
        {
          "type": "list",
          "items": [
            "Operations that previously required code, scripts, or manual configuration file editing can now be performed through the AIO Admin Console, reducing O&M learning costs and implementation overhead.",
            "Starting from this version, the AIO Admin Console will be deployed together with FlightHub in on-premises environments by default."
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "heading",
          "level": 3,
          "text": "5、AIO Admin Console – Experience Optimizations"
        },
        {
          "type": "list",
          "items": [
            "Added display of the FlightHub version number.",
            "Map management now supports configuring layer information.",
            "Supports one-click HTTPS certificate retrieval.",
            "Remote O&M interaction optimized.",
            "Log export now supports selecting a time range."
          ]
        }
      ],
      "parse_warnings": [],
      "stale": false,
      "last_success_at": "2026-06-11T22:33:42"
    },
